WEBVTT

00:02.786 --> 00:04.027
Good morning one church.

00:04.107 --> 00:06.130
How are you guys doing today?

00:06.190 --> 00:31.218
I'm so glad you've taken time out of your schedules to join us for this special online service only that weird Sunday between Christmas and New Year's Day and as we're enjoying the break and I hope you guys are too and have had a festive and very, very Merry Christmas and are preparing to have a happy New Year where just this Sunday morning right here

00:31.394 --> 00:40.684
just hanging out, just wanted to spend some time today, just talking about last year and then what we can do for next year.

00:40.784 --> 00:43.327
But we'll get there in just a minute.

00:44.148 --> 00:49.714
And this week between Christmas and New Year's, it's very strange.

00:49.754 --> 00:50.816
Very strange one for me.

00:50.836 --> 00:52.838
It's like time slows down.

00:53.999 --> 00:57.223
It's this idea, you know, and the leftovers begin to pile up.

00:57.923 --> 01:00.306
I sometimes forget what day it is.

01:00.834 --> 01:12.667
I don't know what day it is, and somewhere between Christmas Day and New Year's Day, we begin to ask bigger questions though.

01:12.687 --> 01:17.893
It's the question of, what am I doing with my life?

01:17.933 --> 01:18.774
Where did the year go?

01:18.794 --> 01:21.937
Man, is this all there is?

01:21.957 --> 01:23.479
Is this it?

01:24.220 --> 01:29.906
But I believe that God often uses this week to whisper something powerful

01:30.306 --> 01:30.927
to his people.

01:32.389 --> 01:38.236
You know, he's whispers, you know, you were made for more than what you settled for.

01:39.697 --> 01:47.447
You were made for more than the battles you lost, the goals you missed, the mistakes you made.

01:47.507 --> 01:52.213
You were made for more because I'm not done with you yet.

01:53.194 --> 01:54.756
He's whispering those things to us.

01:54.796 --> 01:59.762
And today I really want to take an opportunity to step into that truth.

02:00.642 --> 02:03.705
You know, you and I were made for more.

02:04.606 --> 02:09.111
And when I look back at this year for me, I'm gonna have a mixture of things.

02:10.552 --> 02:12.334
And some things I thank God for.

02:13.555 --> 02:17.799
And some, and I just wish I could rewrite a lot of moments there.

02:18.420 --> 02:19.761
This year wasn't simple for me.

02:20.943 --> 02:25.587
It wasn't smooth, but I have to reflect and go, it was shaping me.

02:26.808 --> 02:28.370
You know, there were moments in my life

02:28.770 --> 02:32.475
And this year where I felt God's favor, and strength, and it's blessing.

02:33.757 --> 02:36.741
And man, in some ways, just humbling to me.

02:37.862 --> 02:47.916
And in other ways, in other moments, I felt stretched physically, emotionally, spiritually, and sometimes even financially this year, very, very tough year.

02:49.037 --> 02:53.423
You know, some of my struggles this year, I faced some pressures I didn't expect.

02:54.284 --> 02:58.610
And I had to make some leadership decisions that I didn't ask for.

03:00.738 --> 03:06.225
And I had to have some difficult conversations that I really, really did not want to have.

03:07.667 --> 03:25.671
You know, there were days in ministry that felt heavy and just the weight of navigating tensions and, you know, trying to care for people and shepherd well and lead with wisdom, even though I couldn't see the path or that it just wasn't clear which direction to go.

03:25.731 --> 03:30.738
And, you know, there were moments in my personal life where I felt discouraged

03:32.386 --> 03:34.890
Man, I often wondered if what I was doing was enough.

03:35.551 --> 03:48.092
I was wondering if I was enough, if I was growing enough, if I was truly stepping in to what God had called me to be.

03:48.112 --> 03:58.770
There were seasons and moments in this past year where I felt just overly stretched, you know, between family responsibilities,

03:59.394 --> 04:05.843
care here, pastoral care, small group leadership, major, major business decisions.

04:07.225 --> 04:16.619
Like I said, financial strain and personal expectations that I placed upon myself that I felt I just continue to stack those things higher and higher and just the weight of it.

04:16.659 --> 04:27.314
I faced some uncertainty this year around some major decisions that had to be made with a bicycle shop and closing and moving on and deciding what that would look like.

04:27.490 --> 04:33.678
And what that was very, very difficult time for me and really wrestling with that.

04:34.659 --> 04:40.987
You know, I dealt with relational strain and some misunderstandings and some accountability issues.

04:41.067 --> 04:44.391
And man, sometimes I had to step into some roles I didn't want to.

04:44.432 --> 04:52.722
The roles that required firmness and clarity and grace all at the same time.

04:55.298 --> 05:05.933
And in their days of my life where spiritually I felt that prayer was costly and stillness was very hard to find.

05:08.216 --> 05:14.024
And oftentimes where spiritual warfare felt more real than ever.

05:15.926 --> 05:21.714
And this past year tested my endurance and my patience, my faith and sometimes my trust in Him.

05:23.778 --> 05:29.446
But you know, this year also held successes, real God given, joy giving wins.

05:30.547 --> 05:36.435
I know I saw some growth in areas that really mattered deeply to me.

05:37.537 --> 05:46.449
You know, I saw breakthroughs this year in my relationship with God and in my walk with him and I saw him shaping my identity and my leadership and my voice.

05:49.073 --> 05:52.978
I saw him moving through sermons and teaching and

05:53.218 --> 06:04.253
You know, it's small groups and, you know, the men's group on Monday nights and, you know, just some personal conversations that I was able to have with people that ordinarily wouldn't have had the opportunity to do so.

06:05.294 --> 06:15.768
I saw some growth as a husband and as a dad too, even though my kids are older, it's still the ability to be a good father.

06:15.788 --> 06:23.058
And, you know, although I think that growth was slower than I wanted at times, but it was steady.

06:23.522 --> 06:26.565
And it was real and it was God powered growth.

06:27.466 --> 06:36.716
You know, I saw some discipline form and it's of different ways in my commitment to fitness and some goals that I had and wanted to achieve and seeing those things.

06:36.756 --> 06:41.000
And not just because I love fitness, but because I wanted to be better.

06:42.302 --> 06:50.450
You know, I wanted to face my inconsistencies there and really change my expectations and remove any frustrations I had.

06:50.754 --> 07:05.278
You know, as I began to work and change and do those things, the learning to manage life's pressures with fitness and then the ability to train with intention, you know, to reach a level of fitness that I hadn't seen in many years.

07:05.298 --> 07:10.106
And it was just, it was great just to be able to do that.

07:11.148 --> 07:17.138
I know I built some deeper relationships this year with leaders and friends and inside the community.

07:18.402 --> 07:24.270
And I watched God bringing healing to some places and some reveals some next steps in my faith.

07:26.554 --> 07:30.059
And some next steps in others around me.

07:31.280 --> 07:38.971
And I watched and saw God sustain my family through some of those financial decisions I saw him provide and restore.

07:39.011 --> 07:46.482
And then he just continued to remind me again and again about his strength is made perfect in my weakness.

07:47.426 --> 07:49.188
and to see that and live that.

07:50.830 --> 07:58.399
And when I put it all together, when I see it all put together, my struggles and my successes, here's what I learned.

07:59.640 --> 08:01.403
God waste nothing.

08:03.225 --> 08:06.449
God doesn't waste a thing.

08:08.030 --> 08:14.418
You know, not the pressure, not the late nights, not the frustrations, not the discipline,

08:16.994 --> 08:18.956
Not the training, not the leadership.

08:20.979 --> 08:28.908
He doesn't waste the emotional weight of those tough conversations, though not the moments where I felt stretched beyond myself.

08:28.968 --> 08:30.250
God used all of it.

08:32.192 --> 08:40.622
Every high, every low as a reminder to me that I was made for more, that you are made for more.

08:41.604 --> 08:43.666
You know, we are made for more than what we fear.

08:45.218 --> 08:47.181
We're made for more than what we struggle with.

08:47.601 --> 08:51.406
We're made for more than the battles we fight.

08:54.170 --> 08:57.074
We're made for more than the parts of ourselves that feel unfinished.

08:58.396 --> 09:01.019
You know, I look back and I go, this year did not break me.

09:01.980 --> 09:07.688
It built me because the hand of God was shaping me, forming me, and preparing me.

09:09.390 --> 09:15.058
And the same God who carried me through this year is the same God that is leading me into the next.

09:16.642 --> 09:25.155
And if I'm honest, the more I reflect on my own year, those breakthroughs, the battles, the more I realize something.

09:27.179 --> 09:27.840
I'm not alone.

09:29.863 --> 09:31.546
My struggles are not unique.

09:33.308 --> 09:37.535
My wins aren't isolated and my questions, my frustrations, my hopes.

09:38.557 --> 09:41.141
They're not just my story, they're our story.

09:42.964 --> 09:44.466
They're his story.

09:46.594 --> 09:48.577
because we're being real with each other today.

09:51.682 --> 09:57.570
We all have lives that are mixed chapters last year.

09:58.792 --> 09:59.353
They're mixed.

10:00.855 --> 10:01.877
It's filled with mixed.

10:02.317 --> 10:03.980
You know, some of us walk through success.

10:04.801 --> 10:06.163
Some of us walk through storms.

10:06.924 --> 10:08.667
Some of us did that in the same week.

10:11.511 --> 10:13.554
Some of us ended this year celebrating.

10:14.946 --> 10:16.708
Some of us ended this year exhausted.

10:18.670 --> 10:20.692
Some of us ended this year feeling a little lost.

10:21.973 --> 10:29.881
And I think all of us have moments just like I did where we wonder, am I really where I'm supposed to be?

10:31.843 --> 10:34.966
Did I miss something God wanted me to do?

10:36.928 --> 10:40.091
Is this all that God has for me?

10:42.193 --> 10:43.474
Why do I feel stuck?

10:44.706 --> 10:49.471
Why does purpose feel so far away from me?

10:51.534 --> 11:00.303
And I think because most of us, we believe, and the truth about us is most of us believe that God can do more.

11:01.004 --> 11:01.665
We believe that.

11:01.725 --> 11:03.687
We believe God can do more.

11:03.707 --> 11:04.328
We have that.

11:04.388 --> 11:05.008
We know that.

11:06.370 --> 11:10.194
I think we just struggle to believe that He can do more through us.

11:12.866 --> 11:27.563
Because when we look back, we see the mistakes we made or the times we didn't pray or the opportunities we missed or didn't take the habits that we, that we didn't build or the habits that we did.

11:29.766 --> 11:32.309
Some of those fears that we might not have overcome them.

11:32.329 --> 11:33.570
We just came right to the edge.

11:34.652 --> 11:40.018
You know, we feel like the time was wasted or the, that we fell short.

11:41.890 --> 11:44.313
And sometimes even without realizing it, we begin to settle.

11:46.857 --> 11:49.200
We settle for a routine instead of renewal.

11:49.901 --> 11:52.384
We settle for maintenance instead of mission.

11:53.986 --> 11:55.709
We settle for comfort instead of calling.

11:57.752 --> 12:01.136
We settle for who we were instead of who God says we are.

12:03.319 --> 12:05.782
We begin to think, this is just how my life is.

12:05.822 --> 12:08.466
This is all I'll ever be.

12:10.242 --> 12:13.647
Maybe God does do big things, just not with me.

12:15.350 --> 12:16.392
But, friends, here's the good news.

12:18.475 --> 12:24.585
What we see when we look back and what God sees when He looks at us are not the same thing.

12:27.109 --> 12:30.535
Where we see regret, God sees redemption.

12:32.538 --> 12:34.701
Where we see failure, God sees formation.

12:36.444 --> 12:37.586
Where we see not enough.

12:39.426 --> 12:43.131
God sees the exact place where His power can show up.

12:45.854 --> 12:51.100
And that's why we can't look through our year, the past year, through our own lens.

12:52.102 --> 12:58.329
We have to look at it through His because God has something to say about last year.

12:59.591 --> 13:01.433
God has something to say about your next year.

13:02.674 --> 13:08.882
And God has something to say about you right now in this moment and what He

13:09.122 --> 13:14.731
says is far better, far clearer, and far stronger than anything we say to ourselves.

13:16.413 --> 13:37.106
So before we dive into goals and resolutions and plans for the upcoming year, before we decide what we want to improve or change before the voices of fear, the shame or comparison start to shape our story, I think we got to take time to stop and ask.

13:38.690 --> 13:39.932
What does God say about this?

13:42.335 --> 13:43.496
What does God say about us?

13:45.359 --> 13:53.710
Because if we're going to step into a new year the right way, I don't think we could do it based on how we feel, or even how we think.

13:55.092 --> 13:58.156
I think we must anchor ourselves into what God has spoken.

14:00.980 --> 14:05.706
Because your past may explain you, but God's purpose defines you.

14:06.868 --> 14:08.370
And that's our big idea today.

14:09.346 --> 14:14.112
Your past may explain you, but God's purpose defines you.

14:16.115 --> 14:17.917
I've talked about what I faced this year.

14:17.957 --> 14:21.321
We've talked about what we have faced.

14:23.203 --> 14:29.752
But let's take some time to talk about what God says about who we are and who we're becoming.

14:31.414 --> 14:35.319
Because when we open Scripture, we discover something powerful.

14:36.400 --> 14:38.002
When we look into God's Word,

14:38.530 --> 14:40.333
discover something powerful.

14:42.375 --> 14:43.877
We were made for more.

14:46.221 --> 14:48.945
And not because of our potential, but because of God's purpose.

14:50.627 --> 14:51.248
His purpose.

14:52.389 --> 14:55.033
And not because of our strength, but because of his plan.

14:56.936 --> 14:57.957
We were made for more.

15:01.422 --> 15:02.403
So what does that mean?

15:02.484 --> 15:07.090
What does it look like when we look into scripture and we see what is God saying

15:09.378 --> 15:12.682
through his word to us.

15:12.822 --> 15:15.866
What does scripture say about made for more?

15:16.487 --> 15:18.730
And I want to start today in Ephesians 2, 10.

15:21.854 --> 15:23.436
For we are God's masterpiece.

15:24.918 --> 15:32.127
He created us anew in Christ so we can do the good things he planned for us long ago.

15:36.392 --> 15:37.714
And Paul wrote this and

15:38.306 --> 15:54.886
before anyone had an opinion about you, before you succeeded or failed, before the past year shaped you or scarred you, God spoke purpose over your life.

15:56.708 --> 16:01.614
Right there, you are His masterpiece.

16:03.456 --> 16:08.242
And it's not because you feel perfect or because you performed perfectly

16:09.186 --> 16:16.436
but because the hands that formed the universe formed you and me with intention.

16:18.219 --> 16:20.081
You see, a masterpiece is not rushed.

16:21.283 --> 16:22.365
It's not accidental.

16:23.306 --> 16:24.448
It's not disposable.

16:26.290 --> 16:33.721
A masterpiece is crafted with care and detail, vision and identity.

16:35.423 --> 16:37.426
And it's never meant to be hidden away.

16:39.586 --> 16:41.589
A masterpiece is not meant to be hidden.

16:43.752 --> 16:45.975
You were not made to blend in.

16:48.378 --> 16:52.203
You're not made to live a life of merely existing.

16:53.445 --> 16:55.047
You're not made to just survive.

16:57.009 --> 16:59.393
So we were made to display the work of God.

17:01.335 --> 17:05.240
And that's why Paul says, he has created us anew.

17:08.084 --> 17:09.426
Created us anew, not

17:09.794 --> 17:36.210
Improved not just patched patched up or put back together and not just doing better a new brand new From the inside out You know Jesus didn't come to rescue us so that we could feel Forgiven he rescued us so that we could step into the good things that God planned long ago and

17:38.498 --> 17:59.349
And what I mean, what he's meaning there is that, you know, when we look at those things before the divorce, before the addiction, before the affair, the financial mess, the anxiety and the insecurity, before the things that you'll never tell anyone about, God had already written a purpose into your story.

18:00.911 --> 18:08.402
So if this year felt wasted, you felt like you missed your chance, if you feel like God is disappointed or done with you,

18:10.210 --> 18:12.933
Or maybe you feel like time has passed you by.

18:12.973 --> 18:15.875
I want to hear this clearly today.

18:17.477 --> 18:22.501
And hear it as the voice of the Father, not the voice of your fear.

18:23.703 --> 18:27.066
You see, your purpose, it didn't expire.

18:27.126 --> 18:28.887
It didn't collapse.

18:29.748 --> 18:31.770
Your destiny is not dead.

18:31.850 --> 18:34.032
Your story is not over.

18:35.133 --> 18:40.178
You are still a masterpiece of God and masterpieces do not lose

18:40.322 --> 18:40.943
their value.

18:41.865 --> 18:51.441
Even when time has passed, even when life has been messy, even when you cracked into pressure, you see, the artist is not finished.

18:53.684 --> 18:56.870
The author is not done writing.

18:58.332 --> 19:02.800
And the potter, he has not finished shaping you.

19:04.803 --> 19:06.546
And the good things he had planned for you,

19:07.810 --> 19:10.814
They didn't disappear when the disappoint, disappointments of this year.

19:11.295 --> 19:13.599
They didn't get canceled when you stumbled.

19:15.602 --> 19:18.486
They didn't evaporate because you feel unqualified.

19:19.848 --> 19:20.609
They're still waiting.

19:20.970 --> 19:21.751
They're still ahead.

19:22.051 --> 19:23.053
They're still possible.

19:24.895 --> 19:26.678
And they are still prepared by God himself.

19:28.180 --> 19:31.445
Because we got to remember we were made on purpose for purpose.

19:31.625 --> 19:33.168
And that purpose still stands.

19:34.730 --> 19:37.394
You were made to move forward.

19:39.874 --> 19:42.276
In Isaiah 43, 18 through 19.

19:45.700 --> 19:51.426
Isaiah writes, but forget all that is nothing compared to what I am going to do for I'm about to change to do something new.

19:54.909 --> 20:02.217
It's God's being God meets Israel in that moment of exhaustion and disappointment and discouraging and they're looking back.

20:03.798 --> 20:07.282
They're looking back and rehearsing their past failures.

20:07.554 --> 20:11.278
and replaying the past wounds and remembering their past disappointments.

20:12.920 --> 20:17.765
And right there, in the middle of their looking backward, God interrupts with this command.

20:18.926 --> 20:21.009
Forget all that.

20:22.450 --> 20:37.266
You know, not because the past doesn't matter, not because God ignores your pain, and not because you should pretend nothing happened, but because the past is not where God

20:37.794 --> 20:38.575
want you to live.

20:41.698 --> 20:44.601
You know, you can visit your past, but you're not called to live there.

20:47.284 --> 20:51.208
And I think most of us spent this year living in one or two places.

20:53.370 --> 20:57.834
You know, we lived in the prison of the past pain.

20:58.735 --> 21:05.362
We carry regret of what we did, the grief of what we lost, the shame of who we were,

21:07.394 --> 21:09.077
or the disappointment of what didn't happen.

21:11.500 --> 21:14.845
And the second one is some of us lived in this comfort of past success.

21:16.708 --> 21:20.033
Sometimes success traps us as much as failure.

21:21.355 --> 21:26.323
We cling to old seasons so tightly that we miss the new things God has in store for us.

21:29.468 --> 21:31.691
We miss the new things that to grow into.

21:33.254 --> 21:36.018
See both pain and success

21:36.642 --> 21:40.227
Can't keep us stuck.

21:40.247 --> 21:42.871
But God says right there, forget all that.

21:43.151 --> 21:44.914
I am doing something new.

21:45.635 --> 21:49.861
In other words, don't measure next year by last year.

21:52.004 --> 21:54.207
Don't limit your future based on your past.

21:57.652 --> 22:01.177
And don't assume that what was is all that there will ever be.

22:02.779 --> 22:04.722
See, our God is not a God of stuck.

22:06.050 --> 22:07.993
He's the God of next.

22:08.374 --> 22:09.776
He is the God of new.

22:12.240 --> 22:17.007
If you're breathing this morning, if you are breathing today, then God is still building.

22:19.331 --> 22:21.955
If you woke up, he's still working.

22:21.995 --> 22:27.844
And if there's a pulse in your chest, there's still purpose for your life.

22:27.864 --> 22:34.354
You know, this past year may have felt like wandering and waiting or wasting or breaking or barely hanging on.

22:36.162 --> 22:40.748
But our God specializes in new beginnings.

22:42.189 --> 22:47.916
You know, just because you haven't seen movements doesn't mean that God hasn't been making a way.

22:50.239 --> 22:59.731
Oftentimes, God does His best work underground, preparing, shaping, healing, and restoring, and repositioning.

23:00.973 --> 23:03.075
You see, the next year will not be powered by your strength.

23:04.036 --> 23:05.458
It will be powered by God's

23:05.762 --> 23:07.104
work in you.

23:08.285 --> 23:09.767
We are made to move forward.

23:11.368 --> 23:15.853
So don't let yesterday chain you to a place God has already moved you out of.

23:17.455 --> 23:19.317
You were made to press on.

23:20.278 --> 23:23.282
Paul writes in Philippians 3 12 through 14.

23:25.945 --> 23:33.453
I press on to possess that perfection, which Christ Jesus first possessed in me for getting the past looking forward to what lies ahead.

23:33.473 --> 23:34.194
I press on.

23:37.954 --> 23:40.077
I don't mean to say that I've already achieved these things.

23:40.117 --> 23:50.810
I've already reached perfection, but I press on to possess the perfection in which Christ Jesus first possessed me.

23:52.532 --> 23:55.516
As Paul's writing this, he has every reason to quit.

23:56.837 --> 23:58.259
He has failures behind him.

23:59.641 --> 24:01.163
And he was honest about them when he writes.

24:01.943 --> 24:04.807
He was honest about those failures and he has some battles in front of him.

24:05.508 --> 24:07.250
And he's not pretending that they're not real.

24:09.058 --> 24:13.823
But he also had a calling inside him and that calling pulled him forward.

24:15.385 --> 24:17.387
Paul says, I press on.

24:20.191 --> 24:21.712
Press on.

24:23.254 --> 24:29.161
He didn't say I cruise through or coast in or just drift lightly there.

24:29.621 --> 24:31.083
No, I press.

24:32.985 --> 24:33.826
There's effort.

24:34.567 --> 24:35.468
There's intention.

24:35.888 --> 24:37.490
There's spiritual grit.

24:39.458 --> 24:42.061
There is a holy refusal to settle.

24:42.101 --> 24:42.502
Why?

24:42.922 --> 24:47.748
Because Jesus has more for him and for us.

24:50.952 --> 24:57.319
And for us, because if Jesus had more for Paul, he has more for you and for me.

24:57.359 --> 25:06.610
And some of us think pressing on means trying harder or performing better or fixing ourselves.

25:08.514 --> 25:28.323
But pressing on in the kingdom isn't about earning, it's about leaning, leaning into what Jesus says you are, to what Jesus says you are, leaning into the spirit when you're tired and when you're weary.

25:28.344 --> 25:38.098
If you're uncertain, you lean into scripture, you lean into prayer when you feel overwhelmed and you just, you don't know where to go

25:38.434 --> 25:40.716
When you feel alone, you got to lean into community.

25:42.618 --> 25:46.122
And sometimes we have to lean into obedience even when it's uncomfortable.

25:47.863 --> 25:56.532
Pressing on means I refuse to be who I used to be because Jesus is making me into who I was always meant to be.

25:58.354 --> 25:59.555
Paul says, forget the past.

26:02.057 --> 26:06.642
Not meaning that he erases it, but he refuses to let it direct his steps.

26:07.810 --> 26:12.155
He looks forward, not to wishful thinking, but to the calling of Christ.

26:14.037 --> 26:19.643
There's going to be some moments next year in 2026 when pressing on is a choice.

26:21.245 --> 26:33.899
You're going to be tired, tempted, discouragement is going to whisper, comparison is going to steal the joy and fear is going to say, stop here.

26:35.561 --> 26:36.562
But those are the moment.

26:37.058 --> 26:44.886
When we lean into the Holy Spirit and be reminded that we were made for more than quitting, we were made for more than going back.

26:44.967 --> 26:49.431
We were made to press on because the God who called you is the God who strengthened you.

26:51.734 --> 26:56.739
And the God who strengthened you is the God who finishes what he started in you.

26:57.460 --> 26:58.761
We were made on purpose.

26:59.242 --> 27:00.423
We were made to move forward.

27:00.463 --> 27:02.445
We were made to press on.

27:05.809 --> 27:06.770
So what would it look like?

27:07.458 --> 27:12.125
What does it look like to move into 2026 made for more?

27:14.930 --> 27:15.511
What do we do?

27:16.613 --> 27:19.958
What do we do in 2026 as we begin the new year?

27:22.001 --> 27:25.006
I think there are four declarations that we can make.

27:26.829 --> 27:30.995
The first one is I will not be defined by last year.

27:32.338 --> 27:35.122
Last year might explain you, but it does not have to define you.

27:36.578 --> 27:39.241
Your failures, they don't get the final word.

27:39.481 --> 27:42.625
Your mistakes don't get the microphone and your weaknesses.

27:42.846 --> 27:45.529
They don't get the winning vote, okay?

27:45.549 --> 27:46.950
Your grace gets the final word.

27:48.512 --> 27:54.179
Jesus gets the microphone and the Holy Spirit gets the final vote.

27:55.821 --> 28:00.367
Two, I will choose progress over perfection.

28:02.029 --> 28:06.514
We don't have to fix everything by January 1st, but we can't take a step

28:07.778 --> 28:08.539
Just a step.

28:09.840 --> 28:12.402
Small steps are where big changes begin.

28:13.423 --> 28:14.985
Maybe it's just one prayer a day.

28:16.386 --> 28:18.869
Maybe it's just one step in obedience.

28:20.230 --> 28:23.053
Maybe it's just one habit surrendered.

28:25.195 --> 28:27.958
Or one relationship healed.

28:30.000 --> 28:31.861
Or maybe that's one person that you pour into.

28:33.923 --> 28:36.626
Because small change, small steps,

28:36.930 --> 28:39.873
Small obedience still moves mountains.

28:41.115 --> 28:44.579
Three, I will live for God's purpose, not my comfort.

28:46.000 --> 28:48.323
God did not call us to sit on the couch.

28:51.386 --> 28:52.327
He called us to the kingdom.

28:54.610 --> 28:56.452
In our comfort, we cannot change the world.

28:58.635 --> 29:02.699
But in our calling, in our purpose for our lives, we can.

29:04.621 --> 29:05.202
This year,

29:05.922 --> 29:07.344
Let's step where God leads us.

29:08.965 --> 29:19.016
Even if it's uncomfortable, even if it's inconvenient, and even if it's unfamiliar, because purpose lives on the other side of obedience.

29:20.318 --> 29:23.060
And four, I will trust that God has more for me.

29:24.462 --> 29:31.289
More strength, more freedom, more joy, more maturity, more impact.

29:33.612 --> 29:35.634
And more of His presence in my everyday life.

29:37.986 --> 29:44.536
You can walk into the new year with expectation because we serve a God of more.

29:47.782 --> 30:05.490
And imagine as a church family, what God could do if we all lived this out, if we all were living out our purpose, his purpose for our lives, if each person

30:06.434 --> 30:08.076
stepped into their calling this year.

30:10.077 --> 30:35.762
If each household became a place of prayer, if we fought our sins instead of hiding them, maybe every student believed that God could use them, if every person in our church that is hurting start to find healing, if we just believe that we were a masterpiece

30:36.098 --> 30:37.300
instead of a mistake.

30:38.762 --> 30:41.627
You see, we wouldn't just attend church.

30:41.687 --> 30:45.953
We'd become the church that God designed us to be.

30:48.677 --> 31:00.676
We would see renewal in our marriages, in our families, in our mental health, discipleship, community outreach, the next generation.

31:01.497 --> 31:04.562
We would be a more kind

31:06.178 --> 31:06.699
of church.

31:10.484 --> 31:11.986
We would be more.

31:14.409 --> 31:14.649
We.

31:14.669 --> 31:15.911
And that includes me.

31:16.352 --> 31:17.233
That includes you.

31:19.836 --> 31:27.366
As a step into the final days of this year, the next couple of days, I want you to hear this truth.

31:29.529 --> 31:30.330
I want you to hear it again.

31:30.370 --> 31:33.074
You are made for more than you have been settling for.

31:34.722 --> 31:37.204
You're made for more than life through at you last year.

31:38.966 --> 31:42.369
You're made for more because we're made by God.

31:43.350 --> 31:47.554
We are His masterpiece.

31:47.574 --> 31:53.120
So let go of the weight of the year behind you and lift your eyes to the year ahead.

31:53.180 --> 31:58.305
And as we step into 2026, let's step into it with confidence.

31:59.586 --> 32:02.048
A confidence that God is not done.

32:02.088 --> 32:03.890
God is not finished.

32:04.098 --> 32:05.580
And God is not holding back.

32:08.285 --> 32:10.208
We were made for more.

32:12.011 --> 32:12.792
Let's walk in it.

32:14.374 --> 32:15.055
God, we love you.

32:16.638 --> 32:17.640
We thank you for your grace.

32:17.740 --> 32:18.741
We thank you for your mercy.

32:18.781 --> 32:22.567
We thank you for all the things in our lives.

32:22.648 --> 32:31.762
We thank you for last year, the shaping, the pain, the successes, the failures,

32:33.026 --> 33:02.994
the opportunities we just come humbly before you today as your masterpieces just asking for renewal just humbly laying everything at your feet recognizing that our strength our joy is found in you the victory is yours we just need to continue moving forward as we end

33:03.362 --> 33:09.231
This year, we just ask for continued blessings.

33:10.593 --> 33:31.043
We ask that you look after us next year as we continue to press on our desire to grow closer to you, to be the people that you have called us to be, to recognize that we are made on purpose by you for a purpose created by you.

33:32.024 --> 33:33.266
That we can step into that.

33:33.794 --> 33:53.797
that we could see that purpose clearly, that we keep our eyes fixed on you this year, that we remain in you, in your word, just continue to guide us, lead us, show us the step.

33:57.501 --> 34:02.066
Just ask for encouragement this year for those that are hurting, last for healing,

34:03.810 --> 34:10.978
for those that want to see you, that we could be the people that people see you and not us this year.

34:13.320 --> 34:22.751
They see you in our worship, you in our teaching, you in our speaking, you in our everyday actions Lord.

34:23.812 --> 34:27.536
We ask all of these things and Jesus is powerful and mighty name.

34:28.437 --> 34:28.798
Amen.

34:31.661 --> 34:32.882
Have a happy new year.

34:33.186 --> 34:34.802
Go be the church.

